# Member ordering

Put public API first; private helpers (`_name`) come after.

## Classes

Order: `__init__` → public methods → private methods.

```python
# ✅ GOOD — public methods first, private helper last
class SqlUserProjection(UserProjection):
    def __init__(self, session_factory: async_sessionmaker[AsyncSession]) -> None:
        self._session_factory = session_factory

    async def find_by_email(self, email: str) -> UserReadModel | None:
        ...

    @staticmethod
    def _to_read_model(row: User) -> UserReadModel:
        ...

# ❌ BAD — private method before public API
class SqlUserProjection(UserProjection):
    def _to_read_model(self, row: User) -> UserReadModel:
        ...

    async def find_by_email(self, email: str) -> UserReadModel | None:
        ...
```

## Modules

Order: public classes/functions → module-level private helpers.

```python
# ✅ GOOD — adapter class first, private helpers after
class SqlEventStore(EventStore):
    async def append(self, events: list, ...) -> None:
        ...

def _serialize_event(event: object) -> tuple[str, dict[str, Any], datetime]:
    ...
```

Reference: `infrastructure/adapters/persistence/event_store.py`, `infrastructure/adapters/persistence/projections/user_projection.py`.
